    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Installation
        - Rocker Arm Carrier
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.4.8" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Rocker Arm Carrier</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install dowels in cylinder head.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Dowels may still be attached to the cylinder head.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300599" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08064.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Alignment guides and dowels in place</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Alignment guides</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dowels</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install cylinder head and rocker carrier alignment guides (make locally) in position shown
                prior to installing rocker arm carrier.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft until damper locating dowel hole is in the six o'clock position. This
                positions all pistons below TDC so the valves do not contact the pistons when tightening the rocker arm
                assemblies.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply engine oil to the top center of each valve bridge.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3005102" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08078.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the rocker arm carrier assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place rocker arm carrier onto guides.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove guides and install two rocker carrier bolts (M8 x 50). Tighten each bolt alternately
                while observing rocker carrier, dowel sleeve bushings and cylinder head for signs of misalignment.
                Tighten bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">standard torque
                    <xref refid="S300GTG"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
